




GIT BASIC COMMANDS
git init                                para inicializar el proyecto nuevo o alguno existente.
git add <file> or <files>               para pasar los archivos del working directory al staging area / tambien se usa para actualizar tus archivos activos
git add .                               para agregar todo el folder all staging area
git status                              el estado de tus archivos/proyecto
git commit                              para pasarlos al local repo
git commit -m "add commit comment"
git push                                para subirlo a un repositorio remoto como github
git push origin --delete <branch>	    delete remote branch
git push -u origin <name>	        	push local branch for the first time
git push --set-upstream origin branch   to add your local branch to your remote repo and his code/files
git push origin <branch>                does not link remote and local branches
git push origin <branch> --set-upstream to link local and remote branch
git pull                                para traer los cambios del proyecto remoto al local
git pull                                origin my_remote_branch
git pull origin <branch> --set-upstream link local and remote branch
git fetch                               para indicarte cuales cambias hay en el remote repo
git clone                               descarga remote repo
git rm --cached <file>                  to unstage
git log 
git log --oneline --decorate --all --graph
git restore <file>                      helps to unstage or even discard uncommitted local changes.
git branch                              to create new branches
git branch -u origin/branch            to link remote and local branch
git branch -r	                        list remote branches
git branch -a	                        list remote and local branches
git branch -m <new-name>	            rename local head branch
git branch -m <old-name> <new-name>		rename any local branch
git checkout <branch>                   to change branches
git remote show origin                  to show my remote repo

START GIT PROJECT
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
git config --global user.name "Your Name
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/Ferducar/PowerShell        to modify our origin

PROJECT SETUP
Create a new repository on the command line
git init
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M master
git remote add origin https://github.com/Ferducar/GitTutorial.git
git push -u origin master

Push an existing repository from the command line
git remote add origin https://github.com/Ferducar/GitTutorial.git
git branch -M master
git push -u origin master

Join a team
git clone  <url> <folder name>


  
GIT COMMENTS
Git will ignore empty folders

FEATURE BRANCH GIT AND GITHUB WORKFLOW
Create  a feature branch
upload to git
create pull request
merge feature branch


GITHUB STATES
Working directory > git add > staging area > git commit > repository






